HEADWORD: Doña
<hw>Do"⟦ntil⟧a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>do⟦ntil⟧a</ets>. See <er>Duenna</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lady;
mistress; madam; -- a title of respect used in Spain, prefixed to the
Christian name of a lady.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lady or gentlewoman; -- used in Spanish-speaking
countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Donable</ent>⟦br⟧
